	Tips for teachers        
	Laxmipat Singhania Academy organised a training for nodal teachers under the Adolescence Education Programme (AEP) between October 20 and 22. A training programme for principals was held on October 23. The Central Board of Secondary Education (CBSE) is rescheduling AEP in all private schools affiliated to it. The objective of this programme is to help students cope with the physical, biological and emotional changes that they undergo during their growing years while initiating a sense of self-awareness.              
